Episode 10

12
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:14,710
But why isn't Won coming? Did you really call him?

13
00:01:14,710 --> 00:01:17,810
He'll come. There's no way he won't. It's Ji Chang Soo getting married after all.

14
00:01:17,810 --> 00:01:19,510
Did he get the wrong date?

15
00:01:19,510 --> 00:01:21,460
Hey Ha Na, you don't know where he is either?

16
00:01:21,460 --> 00:01:23,700
He'll probably come.

17
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:27,100
Try calling him. You'll reach him if he's here.

18
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:28,790
- Let's toast.
- Alright.

19
00:01:28,790 --> 00:01:31,630
Cheers!

20
00:01:42,670 --> 00:01:44,680
Hey, Choi Won!

21
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:00,950
I'm a bit late, aren't I?

22
00:02:10,890 --> 00:02:13,780
Did you like your vacation?

23
00:02:13,780 --> 00:02:19,280
Yeah. I also liked the things I wasn't used to.

24
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:22,220
Must have been nice for you.

25
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,640
Jeong Mi is pretty.

26
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:32,080
Chang Soo also seems like a completely different person.

27
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:33,440
I know right.

28
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:37,320
Since we met up after such a long time, let's go to an after party!

29
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:46,070
- Won, eat the peach that I ate.
- Alright, thank you.

30
00:02:46,070 --> 00:02:49,090
Take your sunglasses off! You are the only Spanish!

31
00:02:49,090 --> 00:02:53,060
Hey! How can you just leave without telling anyone you are going on a trip for a month?

32
00:02:53,060 --> 00:02:57,480
Hey! If I told you, you'd order souvenirs and things from the duty free for me to bring back.

33
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:59,960
You freeloaders.

34
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:02,260
You are smart.

35
00:03:02,260 --> 00:03:04,730
Tell us truthfully, Choi Won.

36
00:03:04,730 --> 00:03:09,210
What is your real reason for going on such a long vacation?

37
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:17,200
How should I put it? This trip was to awaken my sleeping five senses?

38
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:23,360
Now that I look at it, the atmosphere between those two is a bit strange.

39
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,460
Did you two fight?

40
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:28,900
Fight? We always fight.

41
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:32,040
You're saying useless things again.

42
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:34,920
Strange. Something's strange.

43
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:36,460
Be quiet.

44
00:03:36,460 --> 00:03:39,100
Something is weird about you.

45
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:41,430
Is it because you have been on an ascetic trip?

46
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:46,110
Hey, you try to walk 820 km and see if you don't become weird.

47
00:03:46,110 --> 00:03:49,920
If I walk that, will I lose weight?

48
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:52,300
I'm not sure, let's think about that seriously.

49
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:58,840
You. You know that Ha Na is dating Cha Seo Hoo again, right?

50
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:04,190
Of course, I do.

51
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:07,580
But doesn't she look like she ages when she dates?

52
00:04:07,580 --> 00:04:09,340
That's for certain.

53
00:04:09,340 --> 00:04:12,200
You're going to fight at this rate again.

54
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,890
Date me now.

55
00:04:13,890 --> 00:04:16,120
Hey!

56
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:18,190
You ugly couple!

57
00:04:18,190 --> 00:04:21,120
It's our first and probably our last wedding day.

58
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:23,060
Our treat!

59
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,870
What a great ambiance!

60
00:04:26,870 --> 00:04:28,690
Let's go for it!

61
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:32,100
♬ Right now let's start to smile, smile again ♬

62
00:04:32,100 --> 00:04:35,560
♬ These are the blissful happy days ♬

63
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:39,240
♬ Shake out your tight shoulders ♬

64
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:41,960
♬ Take the unhappy events and just forget them ♬

65
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:45,870
♬ Forget your sorrows and never cry ♬

66
00:04:45,870 --> 00:04:49,270
♬ Under these hot sunny days ♬

67
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:56,290
♬ Just keep thinking about all the good things that happened and you'll be happy ♬

68
00:04:58,230 --> 00:04:59,690
Yeah?

69
00:05:00,850 --> 00:05:03,290
It's not over yet.

70
00:05:05,110 --> 00:05:08,230
No, I'll go alone today.

71
00:05:09,770 --> 00:05:11,590
Alright.

72
00:05:26,690 --> 00:05:32,750
♫ The image of you brushing your hair up  ♫

73
00:05:33,540 --> 00:05:40,620
♬ Time gradually separates us  ♬

74
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:47,020
♬  Where and why did we go wrong? ♬

75
00:05:47,020 --> 00:05:51,100
No matter what happens, I will come back as a friend who can be on your side.

76
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:57,420
No matter what happens, you have to continue being the gallant Oh Ha Na.

77
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:01,410
Even when I'm not around, eat well and live well.

78
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:10,120
♬  Though our meeting lasted for a short while, I have no regrets ♬

79
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:16,120
♬  No one could replace you  ♬

80
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:24,120
♬  But no is a no, just lingering affection ♬

81
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:29,560
How is it with Cha Seo Hoo?

82
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:32,460
Good.

83
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,960
That's a simple and straight forward answer.

84
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:45,960
♫ Do I need to exchange you with my tears now?  ♫

85
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:52,840
♫ Because I found out your hidden feelings  ♫

86
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:08,460
For one month, did you just walk?

87
00:07:09,380 --> 00:07:13,410
Yeah. As I walked for a long time,

88
00:07:13,410 --> 00:07:17,890
I found out that the sound of my breathing is louder than any other sound in the world.

89
00:07:18,690 --> 00:07:23,330
While listening to the sound of your own breathing, what were you thinking?

90
00:07:23,330 --> 00:07:25,310
You thought I'd be thinking of something, right?

91
00:07:25,310 --> 00:07:28,800
Not at all. I couldn't think of anything.

92
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:34,920
I just wondered, "Should I take a break now? Should I stop walking?" But as that came to mind, I kept walking.

93
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:38,280
What is that?

94
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:44,160
You've changed a bit.

95
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:46,020
How?

96
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:50,700
Should I say you've become manlier?

97
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:53,580
I'm originally a man, you know.

98
00:07:53,580 --> 00:07:59,020
No. You look healthy.

99
00:08:00,810 --> 00:08:06,600
After being away from you for a while, you also look a bit different.

100
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,380
What's different?

101
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:14,570
I didn't really know.

102
00:08:17,170 --> 00:08:19,960
